Koor, Makhteshim, Mizrahi, Spectronix: Israeli Equity Preview

-- B y   S h a r o n   W r o b e l
-- 
2011-06-13T06:38:05Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-13/koor-makhteshim-mizrahi-spectronix-israeli-equity-preview.html
The following stocks may rise or
fall in Israeli markets. Stock symbols are in parentheses after
the company names and prices are from the last close unless
otherwise stated.  The TA-25 Index lost 1.3 percent to 1,204.19 in  Tel Aviv .  Delek The Israeli Fuel Corp. (DLKIS IT): Standard & Poor’s
Maalot lowered its rating on the owner of gas stations to ilA-
from ilA and changed its outlook to “stable” from
“negative.” Delek dropped 3.6 percent to 85.70 shekels.  Delek Drilling-LP (DEDRL IT):  Israel ’s Infrastructures
Ministry granted the energy explorer’s partner Noble Energy Inc.
approval to develop the Noa North natural-gas field and required
drilling and development plans by July 15. Delek Drilling
retreated 3.3 percent to 11.51 shekels. Avner Oil Exploration-LP
(AVNRL IT), another partner in the project, declined 3.2 percent
to 2.043 shekels.  Koor Industries Ltd. (KOR)  : The holding company will pay
other shareholders of  Makhteshim-Agan Industries Ltd. (MAIN)  
$45 million to resolve a class-action lawsuit related to the
sale of Makhteshim to China National Chemical Corp. Koor fell
2.7 percent to 63.64 shekels. Makhteshim dropped 0.3 percent to
17.60 shekels.  Mizrahi-Tefahot Bank Ltd. (MZTF)  : The company’s biggest
biggest mortgage lender, is seeking acquisitions with the aim of
replacing  Israel Discount Bank Ltd. (DSCT)   as the country’s
third-largest bank, Chairman Jacob Perry told Bloomberg. Mizrahi
was unchanged at 35.70 shekels. Discount declined 0.5 percent to
6.47 shekels.  Spectronix Ltd. (SPCT)  : The manufacturer of safety
devices said it won orders worth $4.5 million from the U.S. army
and an unidentified army in  Europe . Spectronix fell 2.5 percent
to 36.89 shekels.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Sharon Wrobel in Tel Aviv at 
 swrobel4@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
